<TITLE> Govt forms Information Commission </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July o1 (bdnews24.com)The government has formed a three-member Information Commission with former secretary M Azizur Rahman at the helm, to implement the Right to Information Act, according to a gazette notification on Wednesday. The other members of the commission include former secretary Mohammad Abu Taher and Sadeka Halim, professor of Dhaka University's sociology department. The Right to Information Act 2009 was passed in parliament on March 29. The new law holds that each and every citizen will have free access to information from government and non-government organisations that will be compelled to divulge the information sought within 20 days of application. The law, however, exempts eight intelligence and law enforcing agencies including NSI and DGFI from making certain information public, but stipulates that the eight agencies are obliged to divulge information on corruption and human rights violations. b
